President Obama issued a statement expressing his condolences to the families of the crew members of the El Faro cargo ship, which tragically sank during a storm. He highlighted the diverse backgrounds of the crew, who were Americans and Poles, and emphasized their dedication and love for the sea. The President acknowledged the important role of merchant mariners in the American economy and pledged the government's support in the investigation of the incident. He also expressed his sympathy for the grieving families and called for unity and support from the community. The President concluded by praying for the crew members and all those who serve at sea.